# Git Cheatsheet

## First time setup
```bash
git init                        # initialize a new repo
git remote add origin <url>     # connect to GitHub repo
```

## Daily workflow
```bash
git status                      # see what files changed
git add .                       # stage all changes
git add <file>                  # stage specific file
git commit -m "your message"    # save changes with a message
git push                        # push to GitHub
git pull                        # get latest changes from GitHub
```

## Branches
```bash
git branch                      # see all branches
git branch <name>               # create new branch
git checkout <name>             # switch to branch
git checkout -b <name>          # create and switch in one step
git merge <name>                # merge branch into current
git branch -d <name>            # delete branch
```

## Useful extras
```bash
git log                         # see commit history
git log --oneline               # compact commit history
git diff                        # see exact changes in files
git stash                       # temporarily save changes without committing
git stash pop                   # bring stashed changes back
git clone <url>                 # download a repo from GitHub
```

## Undo stuff
```bash
git restore <file>              # undo changes in a file
git reset --soft HEAD~1         # undo last commit, keep changes
git reset --hard HEAD~1         # undo last commit, delete changes
```

## Typical push workflow
```bash
git status
git add .
git commit -m "what I changed"
git push
```